<rom>
	<romid>
		<xmlid>RVRbase</xmlid>
		<flashmethod>mitsukernel</flashmethod>
		<memmodel>H8539F</memmodel>
	</romid>

	<notes>
	      2012/11/19 [Tactrix] updated to include missing elements.
	      2024 [Analysis] Extended with additional verified tables from ROM analysis.
	      2025 [Ghidra H8/539F RE] Added TCU/Transmission category from decompilation of
	        tcu_shift_torque_mgmt @ 0x28fff and isr_sci3_eri @ 0x168e3.
	      Address mapping: XML address = file_offset + 0x10000
	      Axis RAM pointers: F0C0=RPM, F0C2=Load/MAP, F0C4=CoolantTempA(ADC),
	        F0C6=AirTemp(ADC), F0C8=CoolantTempB(ADC), F0CA=TimeAfterStart,
	        F0CE=ISCVDemand, F0D0=IAT_raw
	      TCU comms: SCI3 serial channel. ECU sends torque cut commands to TCU each crank pulse.
	        tcu_comms_state (RAM 0xf3d0): 0=idle, 1=rx_wait, 2=tx_active
	        tcu_shift_flags (RAM 0xf3cc): bit0=shift_in_progress, bit1=shift_done,
	          bit2=downshift, bit3=upshift, bit5=sport_mode, bit6=torque_cut_suppressed
	      NOTE on throttle_load_pct (RAM 0xf5de): this is computed as crank period delta
	        (T2GR1H - crank_angle_current) in isr_sci3_eri, NOT a TPS voltage reading.
	        It represents engine load derived from crank timing, not pedal position.
	</notes>

